# TRENCH BEANZ — Server

This little folder is the **server** for your game. It does two jobs:

1. Connects real players together in live multiplayer matches.
2. Stores the real global leaderboard (so scores are shared between everyone).

Your game file (`trench-beanz.html`) goes on **Netlify**.
This server folder goes on **Render**.
They are two separate hosts on purpose — Netlify can't run a server, Render can.

Everything here is free.

---

## What's in this folder

| File | What it is |
|------|------------|
| `server.js` | The actual server program. |
| `package.json` | Tells the host what to install and how to start. |
| `render.yaml` | Optional one-click setup for Render. |
| `.gitignore` | Housekeeping (ignore junk files). |
| `README.md` | This guide. |

You don't need to edit any of these. Just upload the folder.

---

## Deploy it on Render (about 5 minutes)

### Step 1 — Put this folder on GitHub
1. Make a free account at **github.com**.
2. Click **New repository**, name it `trench-beanz-server`, click **Create**.
3. On the new repo page click **uploading an existing file**.
4. Drag in **all the files from this folder** (`server.js`, `package.json`, `render.yaml`, `.gitignore`, `README.md`).
   - Do **not** upload a `node_modules` folder if you have one — it installs automatically.
5. Click **Commit changes**.

### Step 2 — Connect it to Render
1. Make a free account at **render.com** (you can sign in with GitHub — easiest).
2. Click **New** → **Web Service**.
3. Pick your `trench-beanz-server` repo.
4. Render usually fills these in automatically. If not, set:
   - **Build Command:** `npm install`
   - **Start Command:** `npm start`
   - **Instance Type:** Free
5. Click **Create Web Service** and wait ~1–2 minutes for it to build.

### Step 3 — Copy your server address
When it's live, Render shows a URL at the top like:

```
https://trench-beanz-server.onrender.com
```

Copy it, then **change `https` to `wss`**:

```
wss://trench-beanz-server.onrender.com
```

That `wss://...` line is the only thing you need from here.

---

## Connect the game to your server

1. Open **`trench-beanz.html`** in a text editor.
2. Near the top of the multiplayer section there's a line:
   ```js
   const NET_URL='';
   ```
3. Paste your address between the quotes:
   ```js
   const NET_URL='wss://trench-beanz-server.onrender.com';
   ```
4. Save the file and re-upload it to Netlify.

Done. Online matches now use real players, and the leaderboard is shared worldwide.

---

## Good to know

- **It sleeps.** On Render's free plan the server "sleeps" after ~15 minutes with no players. The first person to join after that waits ~30 seconds while it wakes up. Normal for free hosting. If you want it always instant, upgrade to Render's paid plan (~$7/month) or use Railway/Fly.io.
- **Scores are saved.** The `render.yaml` sets up a small disk so the leaderboard survives restarts. If you skip the Blueprint, scores still work but reset whenever the server redeploys.
- **Test it's alive.** Visit your `https://...onrender.com/health` link in a browser — it should say `TRENCH BEANZ server up`.
- **Nothing to set up for offline play.** "Offline — vs AI" in the game never touches this server.

